			<ns0:name>mli...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109474787648168037085/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We don't currently have boost in the SDK.  There are bits of it in the toolchain and those headers do end up in the installed SDK on windows, same way as on linux.  Should boost be added to the SDK as a third_party ... utility?  library?  Do we need compiled components from boost for c_salt or can we use header-only components?  Here is a list of the libraries that currently require compilation in boost.  Everything else can be used as headers only:
Boost.Filesystem
Boost.IOStreams
Boost.ProgramOptions
Boost.Python (see the Boost.Python build documentation before building and installing it)
Boost.Regex
Boost.Serialization
Boost.Signals
Boost.Thread
Boost.Wave</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-02-28T23:15:02.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-02-28T23:15:02.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
